		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=sorourke&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Hello everyone.<br /><br />Started fooling around with some pet classes...and was unsure about something, because I've heard different things regarding giving your pets items.<br /><br />1.) When it comes to a weapon....do you want something with the most damage...or something that's fast?&nbsp;&nbsp;I had heard one account that it didn't matter the delay on the weapon, so you wanted a higher damage weapon....and then I heard the exact opposite.  Keep in mind my particular mage is still in his infancy (non-twinked)...so we are talking rusty 2 handed swords, rusty long swords, etc.<br /><br />2.) Is there any way to see what is on your pet?...along the lines of how we look at our own toon's inventory.  And do they have all the same slots we have for wearing and weilding things?<br /><br />3.) Can anyone recommend another site that has a lot of pet info...such as what abilities the pet has at different levels?<br /><br />Sorry if this has already been covered in previous posts....but it's new to me.<br /><br />Thanks for your help.<br /></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />"Hey man!&nbsp;&nbsp;There's a beverage here!"</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Atlanta</td><td align="right" id="fs8" >3 Replies</td></tr></table>
