		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.25]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=OutlawEyes&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I did learn something about my mage's pet that you might want to bear in mind and perhaps explore.&nbsp;&nbsp;My mage summons a shield-like item (Elemental Defender) that can be placed in either the secondary slot or back slot.  When I equip my pet - armor, lev rings, swords, etc. - I give him his two swords first.  That way, he dual wields the swords and puts the Elemental Defender in the back slot.  If I give him the Defender first, he puts it in his secondary slot and won't wield the second sword.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Central Texas</td></tr></table>
